The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for the analysis of digital pathology images, specifically for prostate cancer detection. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of transfer learning and classification, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of publicly available datasets, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
